WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.165
Acute myocarditis presents with severe hemodynamic

00:00:03.165 --> 00:00:03.693
complications.

00:00:03.693 --> 00:00:06.858
Acute heart failure develops from acute

00:00:06.858 --> 00:00:10.023
ventricular dysfunction and is often refractory

00:00:10.023 --> 00:00:11.606
to standard therapy.

00:00:11.606 --> 00:00:14.771
Fulminant myocarditis may require mechanical circulatory

00:00:14.771 --> 00:00:15.299
support.

00:00:15.299 --> 00:00:18.464
Malignant arrhythmias including ventricular tachycardia and

00:00:18.464 --> 00:00:21.629
ventricular fibrillation account for sudden cardiac

00:00:21.629 --> 00:00:22.684
death risk.

00:00:22.684 --> 00:00:25.849
High-degree atrioventricular block may necessitate temporary

00:00:25.849 --> 00:00:26.377
pacing.

00:00:26.377 --> 00:00:29.542
Cardiogenic shock—the most severe presentation—is characterized

00:00:29.542 --> 00:00:32.707
by hypotension, tissue hypoperfusion, and elevated

00:00:32.707 --> 00:00:35.872
lactate, requiring intensive care and mechanical

00:00:35.872 --> 00:00:36.400
support.
